#11502
Paved road~
From here it is evident that all is not well inside the city.  The walls, once
constructed of smooth grey stone are charred black as though they had been
exposed to some sort of immense heat.  The proud city gates which once would
have held thousands of defenders at bay have been twisted and mangled into
useless lumps of metal.  The pavement here is scorched too, and further west it
appears to have been blasted apart altogether in places.  East is beginning to
look to be the safer way to go.    
