#11503
East gate of Midgard~
Here is what is left of the once proud east gate of Midgard.  Once the home of
many an adventurer, the city was all but destroyed by a bunch of rogue wizards.
After putting paid to the city's defenders, they ransacked and destroyed
everything they could, while leaving just enough of the city standing to be
recognizable as a lesson to any who would cross them in the future.  The gods
were quick to bring down harsh retribution upon the heads of these wizards, but
by that time, the damage had been done.  As punishment, the wizards were
stripped of their powers and made to construct the city of Haven, where most
adventurers live today.    
~
