#11507
Further up the creek.~
The creek bed here passes between what looks like the back of a small house to
the west, and the side of the now deserted treasure shop to the east.  There is
a private jetty to the west which would have been accessible when the creek was
full, but now it is much too high up to reach.  From here you can see that
surprisingly, the turbine is still active, something keeps its blades turning
in a futile attempt to plough through water that isn't there.  North is the
heart of the turbine and south the creek continues back towards the river.    
