#11509
Midgard river~
Nothing but a dried up river bed is left to indicate that this was once the
centre of the mighty Midgard river, which separated the two halves of the city
of Midgard.  There are skeletons of a few dead animals scattered here and
there, a tribute to the awesome power used by the wizards to destroy this
place.  North of here a creek bed stretches out towards what might once have
been a turbine, while east and west the river bed continues.    
