Half way up the cliff~
You have made it half way up the sheer cliff which makes up the north side of
the Eliqua River.  Looking down you can see a sandy inlet, and upwards you
think you spy a castle purched atop the cliff.  The higher you climb, the more
the sense of impending danger increases.  You continue to feel that icy chill,
is it wind?  Or something more sinister?    
