Before the castle~
Standing before the castle you can't help but be impressed with its sheer size
and stature.  The walls are smooth and unclimbable, and the battlements at the
top give the castle's defenders ample opportunity to pick off anyone who thinks
it might be worthwhile trying.  It appears the only way in is through the
portcullus which you are currently standing before.  On either side of the
entrance are two massive hollow pillars inside which the gateguards can shelter
from the cold, or from the light?    
